body:
As a Flutter developer, getting this is pretty confusing:
![screen shot 2016-10-24 at 11 29 57](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/13644170/19640487/38468a10-99dd-11e6-9e4f-decfd5fdccb6.png)

Given they get the Dart SDK via the Flutter SDK, we should see if we can configure the Dart plugin to not show this.

comment_data.body:
cc @alexander-doroshko 

I've been thinking about this too.  In fact, we probably want to remove the update UI from the Dart plugin preferences when configured to use Flutter as well.

Currently we call  `DartSdkUpdateOption.setDartSdkUpdateOption(DartSdkUpdateOption.DoNotCheck);` when setting the Dart SDK via Flutter SDK configuration but since that's not the only path it's not sufficient.
- we could add more calls to cover more cases, or
- we could push some (more) awareness of Flutter into the Dart plugin (added bonus we could suppress the update UI)

/cc @alexander-doroshko

Fantastic!

How do you feel about suppressing or disabling the update UI in `DartConfigurable`?

Thank you!

@mit-mit : do you want to update our blip of known issues to say this is fixed up-stream?

> @mit-mit : do you want to update our blip of known issues to say this is fixed up-stream?

Just leave the label on there, then when we push an update I can query for all closed bugs with the known issues label and see what needs to be updated.

milestone.title: On Deck

title: Disable update prompts from Dart plugin
